One famous urban legend at our school says

in the girls' bathroom, Hanako will answer.

keep a safe distance and watch her carefully.
You'll definitely find an opening!

You can't go up against evil spirits with a bat!
Physical blows will do nothing to them!
But it could be good for destroying objects.

I saw some glowing thing in the 3F hall earlier!
Maybe it's a ghost... *shudder...*

The effect of that warding charm seems weak...
I don't think it'll be much use carrying it around.
Although maybe if it's a weak spirit...

Salt Mandrakes are timid creatures.
Especially with sound - make a sudden loud sound,
and they'll literally faint from fright!

What are you carrying around a Salt Mandrake for?
If it were me, I'd take it to the kitchen and clean it!

The salt from Salt Mandrakes is for cooking,
so it has no warding effect. But who knows?
A young ghost might be tricked and run away!

There was a girl here who loved to play piano.
But no one ever listened, and she died of illness...
Poor girl. I'd gladly hear her performance in full!

Eek! Is that you, \s[1]?!
You're covered in blood!
You should find somewhere to wash off!

Huh? You offered everything already?
That's odd... Why didn't that dispel the curse?
Maybe Mr. Onigawara knows something...

About Salt Mandrakes

Salt Mandrakes are made of salt,

About Mandrake Bombs

"The Puppeteer's Lullaby"

In 19XX, a woman opened a clinic.
"I want to save this world from the nightmare of suffering."
That was her desire.

Yet this desire slowly became warped.
Childhood memories ate at her heart,
awakening desires that had slumbered within.

Notes on the Girl

How long has it been since that girl awoke?
She seems to have inherited memories up to age 9
from the original cells, and looking so healthy and cheerful,
I feel as if she truly is my daughter. Her rare outbursts
may be from a bit of demonic blood being mixed in...

Either way, her fondness for books is the same as ever.
Yet lately, she seems absentminded and sullen.

Might she be lonely without her mother?
Or is something else on her mind?
I'll try to bring it up with her later.

Notes on Twin Dolls

I created twin dolls from my friend's cells.
My daughter wanted friends, you see.

It appears my friend seeks to experiment with the twins.
He seems interested in demons and humans coexisting...
But what do you call our friendship, then?
Does something dissatisfy you?

Not that I care about such things.
I'll just watch these cute twins grow.

Dear friend,
